label: Annotation
definition: Annotation model based on the W3C Web Annotation Data Model (https://www.w3.org/TR/annotation-model/)

label: Id
definition: The handle of the annotation. It is a unique identifier for the annotation. It is composed of the handle of the document followed by a slash and a unique identifier for the annotation.

label: Status
definition: The status of the Digital Object.

label: Job Id
definition: Handle of the job record, if the annotation was produced by a Machine Annotation Service, only filled when annotation was created by a MAS

label: Type
definition: The type of the annotation. It is always ods:Annotation. https://www.w3.org/TR/rdf12-schema/#ch_type

label: Version
definition: The version of the object, each change generates a new version

label: Motivation
definition: The motivation for the annotation. Based on a selection of https://www.w3.org/TR/annotation-model/#motivation-and-purpose. The motivation ods:adding is added for DiSSCo's purposes.

label: Motivated By
definition: Describes the reason for the annotation. https://www.w3.org/TR/annotation-vocab/#motivatedby

label: Has Target
definition: Indicates the particular object and part of the object on which the annotation has been made.

label: Id
definition: This is the PID of the target object. Valid targets are the Digital Specimen, Digital Media Object or another annotation.

label: Type
definition: This is the handle to the type of the target object.

label: Has Selector
definition: Optional field to indicate the part of the target object that is being annotated. It can be a field, a class or a region of interest.

label: Has Body
definition: The body of the annotation contains the specific value of the annotation

label: Value
definition: An array of multiple values in string representation specific for the particular selector

label: References
definition: Indicates how the value came to be. https://purl.org/dc/terms/references

label: Score
definition: A score between 0 and 1 indicating the confidence in the value. 1 is the highest confidence and 0 is the lowest.

label: Creator
definition: Contains an ods:Agent object

label: Created
definition: The date and time when the annotation was created. https://purl.org/dc/terms/created

label: Issued
definition: The date and time when the annotation was generated. https://purl.org/dc/terms/issued

label: Generator
definition: Object containing information on who generated the object. Generated is here seen as who stored/indexed the object. In most case this will be the annotation-processing-service. Contains an ods:Agent object.

label: Aggregate Rating
definition: The average rating based on multiple ratings or reviews

label: Rating Count
definition: The count of total number of ratings. https://schema.org/ratingCount

label: Rating Value
definition: The rating for the content. https://schema.org/ratingValue

label: Batch Id
definition: Internally generated PID to identify the batch the annotation was generated by

label: Merging Decision Status
definition: The merging status of the annotation. Only present when motivation is ods:adding or oa:editing

label: Merging State Change Date
definition: The date and time when the annotation was merging state was changed. Only present when motivation is ods:adding or oa:editing

label: Merging State Changed By
definition: Object containing information on who changed the merging state of the annotation. Only present when motivation is ods:adding or oa:editing. Contains an ods:Agent object.

label: Tombstone Metadata
definition: Object containing the tombstone metadata of the object. Only present when ods:status is ods:Tombstone

label: Tombstone Metadata
definition: The tombstone metadata about the tombstoned digital object

label: Tombstoned Date
definition: Timestamp the Digital Object was tombstoned and no longer active.

label: Tombstoned Text
definition: A reason why the Digital Object was tombstoned
examples: ['This is a duplicate of XXX', 'This object was made by mistake']

label: Tombstoned By Agent
definition: The agent who tombstoned the object, contains an ods:Agent object

label: Has Related Pid
definition: The PIDs of the object the tombstoned object is related to

label: Agent
definition: Description of the agents connected to the digital object

label: Name
definition: Full name of the agent

label: Role Name
definition: Indicates the role of the agent, https://schema.org/roleName

label: Start Date
definition: Date the agent began the role

label: End Date
definition: Date the agent ended the role

label: Role Order
definition: Order of the agent in the role. Can be used to indicate the order of importance

label: Email
definition: Email of the agent, can be present in case the agent is a maintainer of a MAS

label: Url
definition: URL of the agent, can be present in case the agent is a maintainer of a MAS

label: Has Identifier
definition: Contains zero or more ods:Identifier objects
